n. Only when thought has been returned to its rightful “place”—connected to the human species as a whole rather than to individuals—will we be able to escape from the machine that hasimprisoned our lives for far too long.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aPhilosophy, Moderny19th century. 0aPhilosophy, Moderny20th century. 0aPolitical theology. 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 4aPolitical Science. 4aTheology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aContinental Philosophy.  aEconomic Theology.  aItalian Philosophy.  aPolitical Philosophy.  aPolitical Theory.  aRoberto Esposito.  aZakiya Hanafi.1 aHanafi, Zakiya.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311072903040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823267644zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823267644423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823267644/original  a978-3-11-072903-0  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK